{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-doc-page-template-tsx","path":"/docs/hotchocolate/fetching-data","result":{"data":{"file":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/hotchocolate/fetching-data/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Resolver"},"html":"<p>When it comes to fetching data in a GraphQL server you will always end up with a resolver.\n<strong>A resolver is a generic function that fetches data from an arbitrary data source for a particular field.</strong>\nThis means every field has it's own individual resolver function in order to fetch or select data. Even if there isn't a resolver defined for one field, Hot Chocolate will create a default resolver for this particular field behind the scenes.</p>\n<div class=\"mermaid\" data-processed=\"true\"><svg id=\"mermaid-1600376197521\" width=\"254.21875\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" height=\"436.6421813964844\" viewBox=\"0 0 254.21875 436.6421813964844\"><style>#mermaid-1600376197521{font-family:sans-serif;font-size:16px;fill:#333;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .error-icon{fill:#552222;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .error-text{fill:#552222;stroke:#552222;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .edge-thickness-normal{stroke-width:2px;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .edge-thickness-thick{stroke-width:3.5px;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .edge-pattern-solid{stroke-dasharray:0;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .edge-pattern-dashed{stroke-dasharray:3;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .edge-pattern-dotted{stroke-dasharray:2;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .marker{fill:#333333;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .marker.cross{stroke:#333333;}#mermaid-1600376197521 svg{font-family:sans-serif;font-size:16px;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .label{font-family:sans-serif;color:#333;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .label text{fill:#333;}#mermaid-1600376197521 .node rect,#mermaid-1600376197521 .node circle,#mermaid-1600376197521 .node ellipse,#mermaid-1600376197521 .node polygon,#mermaid-1600376197521 .node path{fill:#ECECFF;stroke:#9370DB;stroke-width:1px;}#mermaid-160